 [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]] (loan)\n| caps7               = 14\n| goals7              = 2\n| years8              = 2017\n| clubs8              = \u2192 [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]] (loan)\n| caps8               = 17\n| goals8              = 7\n| years9              = 2018\n| clubs9              = [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]]\n| caps9               = 22\n| goals9              = 3\n| years10              = 2018\u2013\n| clubs10              = [[A.F.C. Fylde]]\n| caps10               = 29 \n| goals10              = 2\n| club-update         = 23:31, 20 May 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Nicholas George Haughton''' (born 20 September 1994) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|AFCFylde}} club [[A.F.C. Fylde]].\n\n==Career==\nAfter being released from Bolton Wanderers, Haughton joined Curzon Ashton FC. Haughton then went on to shine for Trafford FC's scholars which earned him a call up for England Schools. He subsequently began his playing career in the [[North West Counties Football League|North West Counties League]] with [[Runcorn Town F.C.|Runcorn Town]].<ref name=\"loan market\">{{cite web|title=More activity at Highbury this week in the transfer and loan market|url=http://www.fleetwoodtownfc.com/news/article/transfer-and-loan-update-1389677.aspx|website=fleetwoodtownfc.com|accessdate=5 October 2014}}</ref> After a trial at Middlesbrough FC, He joined [[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]] in February 2014 following a trial, and was immediately loaned out to [[Nantwich Town F.C.|Nantwich Town]] of the [[Northern Premier League]].<ref name=\"loan market\"/> He signed a new contract with Fleetwood in September 2014 to keep him tied to the club until 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Youngster extends deal by 12 months|url=http://www.fleetwoodtownfc.com/news/article/haughton-contract-1972629.aspx|website=fleetwoodtownfc.com|accessdate=5 October 2014}}</ref> He made his debut for the \"Cod Army\" in [[the Football League]] on 4 October 2014, coming on for [[Antoni Sarcevic]] 68 minutes into a 1\u20130 win over [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] at [[Highbury Stadium (Fleetwood)|Highbury Stadium]].\n\nIn November 2016 he went out on loan to [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Ammies make Fleetwood midfielder their second loan signing in a week|url=http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/latest-transfer-news/ammies-make-fleetwood-midfielder-their-second-loan-signing-in-a-week.html|work=Non League Daily|date=4 November 2016|accessdate=4 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105034651/http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/latest-transfer-news/ammies-make-fleetwood-midfielder-their-second-loan-signing-in-a-week.html|archive-date=5 November 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018 he joined Salford City on a permanent contract on a two and a half year deal. In late October 2018 he moved to [[A.F.C. Fylde]].<ref>https://salfordcityfc.co.uk/nick-haughton-signs-for-afc-fylde/</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|3 April 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Fleetwood Town F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"NH14\">{{soccerbase season|78154|2014|access-date=16 July 2017}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|22||1||0||0||0||0||0||0||22||1\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Fleetwood Town F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"NH15\">{{soccerbase season|78154|2015|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>\n|League One\n|18||0||1||0||0||0||5<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"FLT\">Appearance(s) in the [[Football League Trophy]]</ref>||0||24||0\n